numerical_variables = ['credit_score', 'age', 'tenure', 'balance', 'estimated_salary']

def standardise_numpy(bccp_df, numerical_variables):
    numerical_data = bccp_df[numerical_variables].values  
    means = np.mean(numerical_data, axis = 0) 
    stds = np.std(numerical_data, axis = 0)   
    standardised_numerical_data = (numerical_data - means) / stds 
    bccp_standardised_df = bccp_df.copy()
    bccp_standardised_df[numerical_variables] = standardised_numerical_data
    return bccp_standardised_df, means, stds

bccp_standardised_df, means, stds = standardise_numpy(bccp_df, numerical_variables)

print(bccp_standardised_df, means, stds)

In [16]:
Q1_estimated_salary = bccp_standardised_df['estimated_salary'].quantile(0.25)
Q3_estimated_salary = bccp_standardised_df['estimated_salary'].quantile(0.75)
IQR_estimated_salary = Q3_estimated_salary - Q1_estimated_salary
lb_es = Q1_estimated_salary - 1.5 * IQR_estimated_salary 
ub_es = Q3_estimated_salary + 1.5 * IQR_estimated_salary

Q1_credit_score = bccp_standardised_df['credit_score'].quantile(0.25)
Q3_credit_score = bccp_standardised_df['credit_score'].quantile(0.75)
IQR_credit_score = Q3_credit_score - Q1_credit_score
lb_cs = Q1_credit_score - 1.5 * IQR_credit_score 
ub_cs = Q3_credit_score + 1.5 * IQR_credit_score 

Q1_age = bccp_standardised_df['age'].quantile(0.25)
Q3_age = bccp_standardised_df['age'].quantile(0.75)
IQR_age = Q3_age - Q1_age
lb_ag = Q1_age - 1.5 * IQR_age 
ub_ag = Q3_age + 1.5 * IQR_age 

es_outliers_mask = (bccp_standardised_df['estimated_salary'] < lb_es) | (bccp_standardised_df['estimated_salary'] > ub_es)
cs_outliers_mask = (bccp_standardised_df['credit_score'] < lb_cs) | (bccp_standardised_df['credit_score'] > ub_cs)
ag_outliers_mask = (bccp_standardised_df['age'] < lb_ag) | (bccp_standardised_df['age'] > ub_ag)

combined_outliers_mask = cs_outliers_mask | ag_outliers_mask | es_outliers_mask 
bccp_outliersremoved_df = bccp_standardised_df[~ combined_outliers_mask]
In [17]:
bccp_cleaned_df = bccp_outliersremoved_df
bccp_cleaned_df.to_csv('Bank Customer Churn Prediction (BCCP) - Dataset (Cleaned).csv', index = False)

BCCP - Predictive Modelling¶

--

Predictive Modelling - Logistic Regression¶

$$ \text{Sigmoid Function: } \quad P(Y = Churn = 1 \mid X) = \sigma(z) = \frac{1}{1 + e^{-z}} \quad \quad z = \beta_0 + \beta_1 X_1 + \beta_2 X_2 + \cdots + \beta_p X_p $$

$$ z = \beta_0 + \beta_1(\text{creditscore}) + \beta_2(\text{country}) + \beta_3(\text{gender}) + \beta_4(\text{age}) + \beta_5(\text{tenure}) + \beta_6(\text{balance}) + \beta_7(\text{activemember}) + \beta_8(\text{estimatedsalary}) $$

$$ \text{Likelihood Function: } \quad L(\beta) = \prod_{i=1}^{n} P(y_i \mid x_i ; \beta) = \prod_{i=1}^{n} \left[ P(y_i = 1 \mid x_i ; \beta)^{y_i} \; P(y_i = 0 \mid x_i ; \beta)^{1-y_i} \right] $$

$$ \text{Parameter Estimation Function: } \quad \hat{\beta} = \arg\min_{\beta} \; [-\ell(\beta)] \quad \quad \quad \text{Gradient of Log-Likelihood Function: } \quad \nabla \ell(\beta) = X^T \big( \sigma(X\beta) - y \big) $$

$$ \text{Gradient Descent Update Formula: } \quad \beta^{(k+1)} = \beta^{(k)} - \tau \, \nabla \ell(\beta^{(k)}) \quad \quad \quad \text{Optimality Condition: } \quad \nabla \ell(\hat{\beta}) = 0 $$

import numpy as np
from numpy.testing import assert_array_almost_equal, assert_array_equal

bccp_lrvariables = bccp_cleaned_df.loc[:, ["credit_score", "country", "gender", "age", "tenure", "balance", "active_member", "estimated_salary"]]
intercept = np.ones((bccp_lrvariables.shape[0], 1))
response = bccp_cleaned_df[["churn"]].values
lr_datamatrix = np.c_[intercept, bccp_lrvariables]
print(lr_datamatrix.shape)

lr_weights = np.zeros(lr_datamatrix.shape[1])
def model_function(lr_datamatrix, lr_weights):
    return lr_datamatrix @ lr_weights

z = model_function(lr_datamatrix, lr_weights)
def logistic_function(z):
    z = np.clip(z, -500, 500)
    return 1 / (1 + np.exp(-z))

def binary_prediction_function(lr_datamatrix, lr_weights, threshold = 0.3):
    lr_probability = logistic_function(model_function(lr_datamatrix, lr_weights))
    lr_binary_probabilities = lr_probability >= threshold
    return lr_probability, lr_binary_probabilities

In [30]:
def objective(lr_weights):
    lr_probabilities = logistic_function(model_function(lr_datamatrix, lr_weights))
    return -np.sum(response * np.log(lr_probabilities) + (1 - response) * np.log(1 - lr_probabilities))

def gradient(weights):
    lr_probabilities = logistic_function(model_function(lr_datamatrix, lr_weights))
    return lr_datamatrix.T @ (lr_probabilities - response)

def gradient_descent(lr_objective, gradient, lr_initial_weights, step_size = 1, no_of_iterations = 100, print_output = 10):
    lr_objective_values = []
    lr_weights = np.copy(lr_initial_weights)
    lr_objective_values.append(lr_objective(lr_weights))
    
    for counter in range(no_of_iterations):
        lr_weights -= step_size * gradient(lr_weights)
        lr_objective_values.append(lr_objective(lr_weights))
        if (counter + 1) % print_output == 0:
            print("Iteration {k}/{m}, objective = {o}.".format(k = counter + 1, m = no_of_iterations, 
                                                               o = lr_objective_values[counter]))
            
    print("Iteration completed after {k}/{m}, objective = {o}.".format(k = counter + 1,
                                                                       m = no_of_iterations, 
                                                                       o = lr_objective_values[counter]))
    return lr_weights, lr_objective_values

def binary_logistic_regression_cost_function(lr_datamatrix, lr_data_labels, lr_weights):
    lr_regression_outputs = model_function(lr_datamatrix, lr_weights)
    return np.mean(np.log(1 + np.exp(lr_regression_outputs)) - lr_data_labels * lr_regression_outputs)

def binary_logistic_regression_gradient(lr_datamatrix, lr_data_labels, lr_weights):
    return lr_datamatrix.T @ (logistic_function(model_function(lr_datamatrix, lr_weights)) - lr_data_labels) / len(lr_datamatrix)

Predictive Modelling - Model Evaluation¶

$$ \text{Precision}_i = \frac{TP_i}{TP_i + FP_i} \quad \quad \quad \text{Accuracy}_i = \frac{TP_i + TN_i}{TP_i + TN_i + FP_i + FN_i} \quad \quad \quad \text{Recall}_i = \text{TPR}_i = \frac{TP_i}{TP_i + FN_i} $$

$$ F1_i = 2 \cdot \frac{\text{Precision}_i \times \text{Recall}_i}{\text{Precision}_i + \text{Recall}_i} \quad \quad \text{Misclassification Rate}_i = 1 - \frac{TP_i + TN_i}{TP_i + TN_i + FP_i + FN_i} = 1 - \text{Accuracy}_i $$

$$ \text{Macro Average} = \frac{1}{|C|} \cdot \sum_{i \in C} \text{Metric}_i \quad \quad \text{Weighted Average} = \frac{1}{N} \cdot \sum_{i \in C} \big(\text{Metric}_i \times \text{Support}_i\big) $$

def confusion_matrix(lr_predicted_labels, lr_true_labels):
    TP = np.sum((lr_predicted_labels == 1) & (lr_true_labels == 1))  
    TN = np.sum((lr_predicted_labels == 0) & (lr_true_labels == 0))  
    FP = np.sum((lr_predicted_labels == 1) & (lr_true_labels == 0))  
    FN = np.sum((lr_predicted_labels == 0) & (lr_true_labels == 1))  
    return TP, TN, FP, FN

def specificity(TN, FP):
    return TN / (TN + FP) if (TN + FP) > 0 else 0

def accuracy(TP, TN, FP, FN):
    total = TP + TN + FP + FN
    return (TP + TN) / total if total > 0 else 0

def precision(TP, FP):
    return TP / (TP + FP) if (TP + FP) > 0 else 0

def recall(TP, FN):  
    return TP / (TP + FN) if (TP + FN) > 0 else 0

def f1_score(lr_precision_value, lr_recall_value):
    return 2 * (lr_precision_value * lr_recall_value) / (lr_precision_value + lr_recall_value) if (lr_precision_value + lr_recall_value) > 0 else 0

def misclassification_rate(FP, FN, total):
    return (FP + FN) / total if total > 0 else 0
